# Review Scope Policy

The authoritative machine-readable review-mode definition lives in `.codex/config/review-scope.yaml`.
Trigger derivation rules live in `.codex/config/trigger-derivation.yaml`.

## Default Mode

Use `delta` review for small, localized changes.

## Delta Review

Review:
- the changed files
- directly impacted modules
- impacted tests

Use delta review when all of the following are true:
- no more than 5 files changed
- no more than 300 total changed lines
- no dependency, CI, database, prompt, or policy surface changed
- the change is not marked as a milestone, release candidate, or architectural change

## Full Review

Use `full` review whenever the work is a milestone or the change is broad enough that local reasoning is not sufficient.

Full review triggers include:
- more than 5 files changed
- more than 300 total changed lines
- `pyproject.toml`, lockfiles, or other dependency manifests changed
- `.github/workflows/` changed
- `.codex/` workflow, policy, or prompt files changed
- database schemas, migrations, or shared interfaces changed
- security-sensitive code paths changed
- the change is explicitly labeled or described as a milestone

Reviewer activation triggers should reuse the normalized trigger vocabulary in `.codex/config/review-scope.yaml` and be derived through `.codex/config/trigger-derivation.yaml`.

If uncertain, prefer `full` review.
